# Sienna Ridge Homes — Tech Stack

## Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 15 App Router (Server Components default) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v3 + Radix UI + CVA |
| Deployment | Vercel — `main` branch = production |
| MLS widgets | RealScout web components (`AGENT_ENCODED_ID` from `lib/site-config.ts`) |
| SEO | JSON-LD in `lib/structured-data.ts`, sitemaps in `app/sitemap*.xml/` |
| Analytics | Google Analytics `G-VB9NKRDQK1` via `components/third-party-scripts.tsx` |

## Conventions

- **Imports**: top of file only; use `@/` path alias.
- **Site constants**: NAP, URLs, agent ID live in `lib/site-config.ts` — never hardcode.
- **Structured data**: build with helpers in `lib/structured-data.ts`; render via `components/json-ld.tsx`.
- **RealScout**: load once via `components/realscout-script.tsx` (`lazyOnload`); do not duplicate `<Script>` tags on pages.
- **Listings**: featured models in `lib/listings-data.ts`; detail pages at `app/listings/[slug]/`.
- **Reviews**: testimonials in `lib/reviews-data.ts`; use `ClientReviewsSection` with matching schema.
- **Sitemap URLs**: register in `lib/sitemap-pages.ts` only.
- **Commits**: push directly to `main` for production deploys.

## Do not

- Add fake `aggregateRating` or MLS numbers without real data.
- Use `getServerSideProps` / Pages Router patterns.
- Create nested git repos or duplicate project roots.
- Defer JSON-LD with `afterInteractive` — use server-rendered `JsonLd` component.
